You will see that there is a red oddly shaped figure, That's the Liver. the Liver is the second most complex organ in the human body, It serves over 500 jobs, including making Bile. text:
When light hits an object , it bounces off and gets reflected into your eyes. the light-bending parts in your eye are called the lens and cornea . they focus light onto your retina.
In most peoples eyes , images are refected perfectly onto the retina. bet some ppeoples corneas aren't shaped right , so they focus the imageinfront of the retina . when that happens the image looks blurry and the person is said to be myopic or nearsighted .
other people have corneas that focus light behind the retina , these people are said to be hyperopic or farsighted .
